st to threaten ... one has to go down into what one most fears and in that process ... comes a saving flicker of light and energy that  even if it does not produce the courage of a hero  at any rate enables a trembling mortal to take one step further.', 19955, 0), (418740, 'I was afraid to write Fear of Flying  ergo  I had to write it. I have lived my life according to this principle: If I''m afraid of it  then I must do it.', 405, 0), (418741, 'One ought never to turn one''s back on a threatened danger and try to run away from it. If you do that  you will double the danger. But if you meet it promptly and without flinching  you will reduce the danger by half. Never run away from anything. Never!', 3621, 0), (418742, 'Being "brave" means doing or facing something frightening. ... Being "fearless" means being without fear.', 63098, 0), (418743, 'From a distance it is something  and nearby it is nothing.', 2843, 0), (418744, 'What you are afraid to do is a clear indicator of the next thing you need to do.', 33, 0), (418745, 'He that is afraid to shake the dice will never throw a six.', 7652, 0), (418746, 'The most drastic  and usually the most effective  remedy for fear is direct action.', 65826, 0), (418747, 'To be busy with material affairs is the best preservative against reflection  fears  doubts.... I suppose a fellow proposing to cut his throat would experience a sort of relief while occupied in stropping his razor carefully.', 1241, 0), (418748, 'I think we should follow a simple rule: if we can take the worst  take the risk.', 62254, 0), (418749, 'Happiness is to take up the struggle in the midst of the raging storm  not to pluck the lute in the moonlight or recite poetry among the blossoms.', 65827, 0), (418750, 'Winners take chances. Like everyone else  they fear failing  but they refuse to let fear control them.', 65828, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (418751, 'Many of our fears are tissuepaper-thin  and a single courageous step would carry us clear through them.', 37592, 0), (418752, 'The habit of doing one''s duty drives away fear.', 1165, 0), (418753, 'Become so wrapped up in something that you forget to be afraid.', 59899, 0), (418754, 'Things done well and with care exempt themselves from fear.', 13, 0), (418755, 'Ultimately we know deeply that the other side of every fear is freedom.', 62855, 0), (418756, 'One had to take some action against fear when once it laid hold of one.', 36, 0), (418757, 'Too busy with the crowded hour to fear to live or die.', 760, 0), (418758, 'A life of action and danger moderates the dread of death. It not only gives us fortitude to bear pain  but teaches us at every step the precarious tenure on which we hold our present being.', 8948, 0), (418759, 'If you want to conquer fear  don''t sit at home and think about it. Go out and get busy.', 1005, 0), (418760, 'Half our fears are baseless  the other half discreditable.', 7233, 0), (418761, 'We poison our lives with fear of burglary and shipwreck and ... the house is never burgled  and the ship never goes down.', 713, 0), (418762, 'To relinquish a present good through apprehension of a future evil is in most instances unwise ... from a fear which may afterwards turn out groundless  you lost the good that lay within your grasp.', 7615, 0), (418763, 'Envy and fear are the only passions to which no pleasure is attached.', 63642, 0), (418764, 'There is often less danger in the things we fear than in the things we desire.', 63642, 0), (418765, 'Needless fear and panic over disease or misfortune that seldom materialize are simply bad habits. By proper ventilation and illumination of the mind it is possible to cultivate tolerance  poise and real courage.', 62509, 0), (418766, 'There are very few monsters who warrant the fear we have of them.', 8, 0), (418767, 'When thinking won''t 