ear is the absence of faith.', 2750, 0), (418783, 'Faith in yourself and faith in God are the key to mastery of fear.', 65832, 0), (418784, 'God is our refuge and strength  a very present help in trouble. Therefore we will not fear.', 5587, 0), (418785, 'I will not fear  for you are ever with me  and you will never leave me to face my perils alone.', 123, 0), (418786, 'Fear is faithlessness.', 3992, 0), (418787, 'I stopped believing in Santa Claus when I was six. Mother took me to see him in a department store and he asked for my autograph.', 65833, 0), (418788, 'Nothing recedes like success.', 15436, 0), (418789, 'Perseverance  n.: A lowly virtue whereby mediocrity achieves a glorious success.', 224, 0), (418790, 'Success for the striver washes away the effort of striving.', 16113, 0), (418791, 'The penalty of success is to be bored by people who used to snub you.', 65834, 0), (418792, 'The secret of success is constancy to purpose.', 1827, 0), (418793, 'There are few successful adults who were not first successful children.', 58721, 0), (418794, 'What is success? To laugh often and much  To win the respect of intelligent people and the affection of children  To earn the appreciation of honest critics and endure the betrayal of false friends  To appreciate beauty  To find the best in others  To leave the world a bit better  whether by a healthy child  a garden patch or a redeemed social condition  To know even one life has breathed easier because you have lived  That is to have succeeded.', 760, 0), (418795, 'If one advances confidently in the direction of his dreams  and endeavours to live the life which he has imagined  he will meet with a success unexpected in common hours.', 1049, 0), (418796, 'The world belongs to the enthusiast who keeps cool.', 40648, 0), (418797, 'Out of every fruition of success  no matter what  comes forth something to make a new effort necessary.', 1127, 0), (418798, 'Though a tree grow ever so high  the falling leaves return to the root