ess usually comes to those who are too busy to be looking for it.', 1049, 0), (418986, 'Excellence in any pursuit is the late  ripe fruit of toil.', 65856, 0), (418987, 'It''s in the preparation-in those dreary pedestrian virtues they taught you in seventh grade and you didn''t believe. It''s making the extra call and caring a lot.', 64891, 0), (418988, 'In all human affairs there are efforts  and there are results  and the strength of the effort is the measure of the result.', 14092, 0), (418989, 'It is no use saying "we are doing our best." You have got to succeed in doing what is necessary.', 3621, 0), (418990, 'Social advance depends as much upon the process through which it is secured as upon the result itself.', 21138, 0), (418991, 'Until they are of the age to use the brain.', 157, 0), (418992, 'Crime seems to change character when it crosses a bridge or a tunnel. In the city  crime is taken as emblematic of class and race. In the suburbs  though  it''s intimate and psychological-resistant to generalization  a mystery of the individual soul.', 10605, 0), (418993, 'Since when do grown men and women  who presume to hold high government office and exercise what they think of as "moral leadership " require ethics officers to tell them whether it is or isn''t permissible to grab the secretary''s behind or redirect public funds to their own personal advantage?', 65668, 0), (418994, 'Vice Is nice But a little virtue Won''t hurt you.', 65857, 0), (418995, 'The lesser evil is also evil.', 33756, 0), (418996, 'The great majority of successful business men and women have been and are possessors of strong personalities of the right sort  and by analyzing their climb to success it is amazing to discover how large a part good manners  good breeding  and correct behavior have had in helping them to win the goal.', 65858, 0), (418997, 'I don''t eat junk food and I don''t think junk thoughts.', 47088, 0), (418998, 'The Department of Justice is committed to asking one central 