INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (419001, 'Noble deeds and hot baths are the best cures for depression.', 684, 0), (419002, 'Will you be satisfied with the fruit of your life''s work? Will the efforts you are making now bring you satisfaction when the things of time are receding  and eternity looms ahead?', 65859, 0), (419003, 'The act of acting morally is behaving as if everything we do matters.', 1739, 0), (419004, 'I place a high moral value on the way people behave. I find it repellent to have a lot  and to behave with anything other than courtesy in the old sense of the word-politeness of the heart  a gentleness of the spirit.', 689, 0), (419005, 'Success ... depends on your ability to make and keep friends.', 62647, 0), (419006, 'Some men succeed by what they know  some by what they do  and a few by what they are.', 4, 0), (419007, 'Try not to become a man of success  but rather a man of value.', 104, 0), (419008, 'It is abundantly clear that success tends to negate humility.', 65860, 0), (419009, 'Success seems to be that which forms the distinction between confidence and conceit.', 432, 0), (419010, 'The common idea that success spoils people by making them vain  egotistic  and self-complacent is erroneous  on the contrary  it makes them  for the most part  humble  tolerant  and kind. Failure makes people cruel and bitter.', 235, 0), (419011, 'Character cannot be developed in ease and quiet. Only through experience of trial and suffering can the soul be strengthened  vision cleared  ambition inspired  and success achieved.', 701, 0), (419012, 'If a man be self-controlled  truthful  wise  and resolute  is there aught that can stay out of reach of such a man?', 63818, 0), (419013, 'Character is the real foundation of all worthwhile success.', 65861, 0), (419014, 'One of the first businesses of a sensible man is to know when he is beaten  and to leave off fighting at once.', 4111, 0), (419015, 'If you can''t accept losing  you can''t win.', 5571, 0), (419016, 'You can''t have any successes unless you can accept failure.', 63524, 0), (419017, 'We have fought this fight as long  and as well  as we know how. We have been defeated ... there is now but one course to pursue. We must accept the situation.', 1924, 0), (419018, 'The most considerable difference I note among men is not in their readiness to fall into error  but in their readiness to acknowledge these inevitable lapses.', 1852, 0), (419019, 'An error gracefully acknowledged is a victory won.', 63451, 0), (419020, 'The man who can own up to his error is greater than he who merely knows how to avoid making it.', 63512, 0), (419021, 'I have made mistakes  but I have never made the mistake of claiming that I never made one.', 63511, 0), (419022, 'I am not the smartest or most talented person in the world  but I succeeded because I keep going  and going  and going.', 35699, 0), (419023, 'Victory belongs to the most persevering.', 1702, 0), (419024, 'You can imprison a man  but not an idea. You can exile a man  but not an idea. You can kill a man  but not an idea.', 16721, 0), (419025, 'It never pays to deal with the flyweights of the world. They take far too much pleasure in thwarting you at every turn.', 2231, 0), (419026, 'I know the price of success: dedication  hard work and an unremitting devotion to the things you want to see happen.', 1836, 0), (419027, 'There is no point at which you can say  "Well  I''m successful now. I might as well take a nap."', 1288, 0), (419028, 'I wrote for twelve years and collected 250 rejection slips before getting any fiction published  so I guess outside reinforcement isn''t all that important to me.', 20537, 0), (419029, 'I used to want the words "She tried" on my tombstone. Now I want "She did it."', 32561, 0), (419030, 'Success generally depends upon knowing how long it takes to succeed.', 48659, 0), (419031, 'I am not afraid of the pen  or the scaffold  or the sword. I will tell the truth whenever I please.', 65862, 0), (419032, 'Once I decide to do something  I can''t have people telling me I can''t. If there''s a roadblock  you jump over it  walk around it  crawl under it.', 65863, 0), (419033, 'Success seems to be largely a matter of hanging on after others have let go.', 5249, 0), (419034, 'Call the roll in your memory of conspicuously successful business giants and ... you will be struck by the fact that almost every one of them encountered inordinate difficulties sufficient to crush all but the gamest of spirits. Edison went hungry many times before he became famous.', 14130, 0), (419035, 'Problems arise in that one has to find a balance between what people need from you and what you need for yourself.', 65864, 0), (419036, 'If your efforts are sometimes greeted with indifference  don''t lose heart. The sun puts on a wonderful show at daybreak  yet most of the people in the audience go on sleeping.', 65865, 0), (419037, 'If you wish success in life  make perseverance your bosom friend.', 2868, 0), (419038, 'Perseverance is failing nineteen times and succeeding the twentieth.', 62854, 0), (419039, 'The only thing that happens overnight is recognition. Not talent.', 65866, 0), (419040, 'If you rest  you rust.', 4743, 0), (419041, 'If you don''t quit  and don''t cheat  and don''t run home when trouble arrives  you can only win.', 65867, 0), (419042, 'They who are the most persistent  and work in the true spirit  will invariably be the most successful.', 7329, 0), (419043, 'If at first you don''t succeed  try  try  try again.', 64856, 0), (419044, 'If at first you don''t succeed  you''re running about average.', 64857, 0), (419045, 'The only way to the top is by persistent  intelligent  hard work.', 64858, 0), (419046, 'The heights by great men reached and kept Were not attained by sudden flight  But they  while their companions slept Were toiling upward in the night.', 147, 0), (419047, 'I realized early on that success was tied to not giving up. Most people in t