hat is needed of it by the Divine forces.', 62239, 0), (419637, 'See how time makes all grief decay.', 62317, 0), (419638, 'The only limit to our realization of tomorrow will be our doubts of today. Let us move forward with strong and active faith.', 63327, 0), (419639, 'It is not the cares of today  but the cares of tomorrow  that weigh a man down. For the needs of today we have corresponding strength given. For the morrow we are told to trust. It is not ours yet.', 3992, 0), (419640, 'Take therefore no thought of the morrow  for the morrow shall take thought for the things of itself.', 5587, 0), (419641, 'Tomorrow is the day when idlers work  and fools reform  and mortal men lay hold on heaven.', 4028, 0), (419642, 'Tomorrow is the mysterious  unknown guest.', 147, 0), (419643, 'Tomorrow is the only day in the year that appeals to a lazy man.', 65926, 0), (419644, 'The future is something which everyone reaches at the rate of sixty minutes an hour  whatever he does  whoever he is.', 26, 0), (419645, 'The future is a world limited by ourselves-in it we discover only what concerns us.', 2006, 0), (419646, 'The future is only the past again  entered through another gate.', 7353, 0), (419647, 'The future is the most expensive luxury in the world.', 744, 0), (419648, 'The future is the shape of things to come.', 3173, 0), (419649, 'The future is the past in preparation.', 65927, 0), (419650, 'To the being of fully alive  the future is not ominous but a promise  it surrounds the present like a halo.', 2575, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (419651, 'The future is hope!', 65928, 0), (419652, 'The future is a great land.', 33, 0), (419653, 'The future is wider than vision  and has no end.', 62297, 0), (419654, 'Losing the future is the best thing that ever happened to me.', 16214, 0), (419655, 'Grow old along with me! The best is yet to be.', 698, 0), (419656, 'I have always been driven by some distant music-a battle hymn no doubt-for I have been at war from the beginning. I''ve never looked back before. I''ve never had the time and it has always seemed so dangerous.', 13058, 0), (419657, 'He who lives in the future lives in a featureless blank  he lives in impersonality  he lives in Nirvana. The past is democratic  because it is a people. The future is despotic  because it is a caprice. Every man is alone in his prediction  just as each man is alone in a dream.', 263, 0), (419658, 'The future belongs to those who believe in the beauty of their dreams.', 141, 0), (419659, 'When I look to the future  it''s so bright  it burns my eyes.', 588, 0), (419660, 'I like the dreams of the future better than the history of the past.', 1207, 0), (419661, 'I never think of the future. It comes soon enough.', 104, 0), (419662, 'You cannot plan the future by the past.', 2026, 0), (419663, 'It is when tomorrow''s burden is added to the burden of today that the weight is more than a man can bear.', 3992, 0), (419664, 'My interest is in the future because I am going to spend the rest of my life there.', 41716, 0), (419665, 'Yesterday is not ours to recover  but tomorrow is ours to win or lose.', 1763, 0), (419666, 'The possibilities for tomorrow are usually beyond our expectations.', 33, 0), (419667, 'Where will I be five years from now? I delight in not knowing. That''s one of the greatest things about life-its wonderful surprises.', 63309, 0), (419668, 'When I look at the future  it''s so bright  it burns my eyes.', 588, 0), (419669, 'Everyone''s future is  in r