nd recreate the passion.', 23, 0), (419784, 'The biggest thing in today''s sorrow is the memory of yesterday''s joy.', 81, 0), (419785, 'It''s but little good you''ll go a-water-ing the last year''s crop.', 215, 0), (419786, 'The worst thing you can do is to try to cling to something that''s gone  or to recreate it.', 62324, 0), (419787, 'Ne''er look for the birds of this year in the nests of the last.', 62284, 0), (419788, 'Don''t look back. Something may be gaining on you.', 5228, 0), (419789, 'Anyone who limits her vision to memories of yesterday is already dead.', 5328, 0), (419790, 'I like the dreams for the future better than the history of the past.', 1207, 0), (419791, 'The first recipe for happiness is: Avoid too lengthy meditations on the past.', 10019, 0), (419792, 'The past is a funeral gone by.', 9328, 0), (419793, 'Never let yesterday use up today.', 65943, 0), (419794, 'How the past perishes is how the future becomes.', 2606, 0), (419795, 'The dogmas of the quiet past are inadequate to the stormy present.', 1012, 0), (419796, 'In the life of the spirit there is no ending that is not a beginning.', 65944, 0), (419797, 'The past is but the beginning of a beginning  and all that is and has been is but the twilight of the dawn.', 3173, 0), (419798, 'Anyone who limits her vision to memories of yesterday is already dead.', 5328, 0), (419799, 'Nor deem the irrevocable Past As wholly wasted  wholly vain  If  rising on its wrecks  at last To something nobler we attain.', 147, 0), (419800, 'Youth is  after all  just a moment  but it is the moment  the spark that you always carry in your heart.', 65945, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (419801, 'Nothing is predestined: The obstacles of your past can become the gateways that lead to new beginnings.', 65946, 0), (419802, 'No star is ever lost we once have seen  We always may be what we might have been.', 62317, 0), (419803, 'What''s past is prologue.', 13, 0), (419804, 'In my end is my beginning.', 65947, 0), (419805, 'The good old days were never that good  believe me. The good new days are today  and better days are coming tomorrow. Our greatest songs are still unsung.', 15498, 0), (419806, 'The past is never completely lost  khowever extensive the devastation. Your sorrows are the bricks and mortar of a magnificent temple. What you are today and what you will be tomorrow are because of what you have been.', 65948, 0), (419807, 'Fear not for the future  weep not for the past.', 165, 0), (419808, 'There are two days about which nobody should ever worry  and these are yesterday and tomorrow.', 65949, 0), (419809, 'We crucify ourselves between two thieves: regret for yesterday and fear of tomorrow.', 47746, 0), (419810, 'Every saint has a past  and every sinner has a future.', 40, 0), (419811, 'When I am anxious it is because I am living in the future. When I am depressed it is because I am living in the past.', 33, 0), (419812, 'I''m not convinced that the world is in any worse shape than it ever was. It''s just that in this age of almost instantaneous communication  we bear the weight of problems our forefathers only read about after they were solved.', 65950, 0), (419813, 'Truth has no beginning.', 5264, 0), (419814, 'The world''s history is constant  like the laws of nature  and simple  like the souls of men.', 62240, 0), (419815, 'These are the stories that never  never die  that are carried like seed into a new country  are told to you and me and make in us new and lasting strengths.', 63764, 0), (419816, 'What one loves in childhood stays in the heart forever.', 3931, 0), (419817, 'This time  like all times  is a very good one if we but know what to do with it.', 760, 0), (419818, 'In times like these  it helps to recall that there have always been times like these.', 30665, 0), (419819, 'Our ignorance of history makes us libel our own times. People have always been like this.', 647, 0), (419820, 'The good old days are neither better nor worse than the ones we''re living through right now.', 65951, 0), (419821, 'Where I was born and where and how I have lived is unimportant. It is what I have done with where I have been that should be of interest.', 1944, 0), (419822, 'Respect the past in the full measure of its deserts  but do not make the mistake of confusing it with the present  nor seek in it the ideals of the future.', 65952, 0), (419823, 'It''s a pleasure to share one''s memories. Everything remembered is dear  endearing  touching  precious. At least the past is safe-though we didn''t know it at the time. We know it now. Because it''s in the past  because we have survived.', 4673, 0), (419824, 'The events in our lives happen in a sequence in time  but in their significance to ourselves  they find their own order ... the continuous thread of revelation.', 1666, 0), (419825, 'The best compliment we can pay our past is to prophetically and bravely face today and tomorrow.', 65953, 0), (419826, 'Some memories are realities  and are better than anything that can ever happen to one again.', 307, 0), (419827, 'Fortunate are the people whose roots are deep.', 65569, 0), (419828, 'As the dew to the blossom  the bud to the bee  As the scent to the rose  are those memories to me.', 65954, 0), (419829, 'Heirlooms we don''t have in our family. But stories we''ve got.', 62384, 0), (419830, 'We have to do with the past only as we can make it useful to the present and the future.', 7432, 0), (419831, 'The past is a guidepost  not a hitching post.', 63458, 0), (419832, 'The past in retrospect holds manifold disenchantments  failures and even tragedies  and yet the worse may be forgotten and the best held fast.', 65955, 0), (419833, 'The road was new to me  as roads always are  going back.', 844, 0), (419834, 'No yesterdays are ever wasted for those who give themselves to today.', 37592, 0), (419835, 'Yesterday I lived  today I suffer  tomorrow I die  but I still think fondly  today and tomorrow  of yesterday.', 3244, 0), (419836, 'Each has his past shut in him like the leaves of a book shown to him by heart  and his friends can only read the title.', 113, 0), (419837, 'We are well advised to keep on nodding terms with the people we used to be  whether we find them attractive company or not.... We forget all too soon the things we thought we could never forget.', 1170, 0), (419838, 'The past is a work of art  free of irrelevancies and loose ends.', 17074, 0), (419839, 'The past is a foreign country  they do things differently there.', 65956, 0), (419840, 'The past with its pleasures  its rewards  its foolishness  its punishments  is there for each of us forever  and it should be.', 1991, 0), (419841, 'The past is that which we possess fully and in whole.', 65957, 0), (419842, 'Our deeds still travel with us from afar  and what we have been makes us what we are.', 215, 0), (419843, 'The past is the tomorrow that got away.', 65958, 0), (419844, 'Our life is like some vast lake that is slowly filling with the stream of our years. As the waters creep surely upward the landmarks of the past are one by one submerged. But there shall always be memory to lift its head above the tide until the lake is overflowing.', 65959, 0), (419845, 'Why should we grope among the dry bones of the past  or put the living generation into masquerade out of its faded wardrobe?', 760, 0), (419846, 'No past is dead for us  but only sleeping  love.', 25904, 0), (419847, 'I look back on my life like a good day''s work  it is done and I am satisfied with it.', 1614, 0), (419848, 'Of all sad words of tongue or pen  the saddest are these: It might have 