ne of these days.', 63109, 0), (419885, 'This is the day which the Lord has made. Let us rejoice and be glad in it.', 5587, 0), (419886, 'He growled at morning  noon  and night  And trouble sought to borrow  Although today the sky was bright  He knew t''would storm tomorrow  A thought of joy he could not stand  And struggled to resist it  Though sunshine dappled all the land This sorry pessimist it.', 65964, 0), (419887, 'To those leaning on the sustaining infinite  to-day is big with blessings.', 5264, 0), (419888, 'The here-and-now is no mere filling of time  but a filling of time with God.', 63257, 0), (419889, 'In the present  every day is a miracle.', 19531, 0), (419890, 'Life is only this place  this time  and these people right here and now.', 48317, 0), (419891, 'I believe that only one person in a thousand knows the trick of really living in the present.', 20188, 0), (419892, 'There is one thing we can do  and the happiest people are those who do it to the limit of their ability. We can be completely present. We can be all here. We can ... give all our attention to the opportunity before us.', 11546, 0), (419893, 'The more I give myself permission to live in the moment and enjoy it without feeling guilty or judgmental about any other time  the better I feel about the quality of my work.', 21729, 0), (419894, 'Act-act in the living Present!', 147, 0), (419895, 'Are not my days few? Cease then  and let me alone  that I may take comfort a little  Before I go to the place from which I shall not return.', 5587, 0), (419896, 'Now or never was the time.', 1719, 0), (419897, 'And now  Lord  what wait I for?', 5587, 0), (419898, 'The future belongs to those who live intensely in the present.', 33, 0), (419899, 'The present is elastic to embrace infinity.', 65965, 0), (419900, 'The present is the living sum-total of the whole past.', 3061, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (419901, 'The present is an eternal now.', 428, 0), (419902, 'The present is all the ready money Fate can give.', 428, 0), (419903, 'The present is an edifice which God cannot rebuild.', 760, 0), (419904, 'The present is the blocks with which we build.', 147, 0), (419905, 'The present is the symbol and vehicle of the future.', 65966, 0), (419906, 'The present is all you have for your certain possession.', 33, 0), (419907, 'We are here and it is now. Further than that  all knowledge is moonshine.', 411, 0), (419908, 'Having spent the better part of my life trying either to relive the past or experience the future before it arrives  I have come to believe that in between these two extremes is peace.', 33, 0), (419909, 'This time  like all times  is a very good one if we but know what to do with it.', 760, 0), (419910, 'The time is always right to do what is right.', 21767, 0), (419911, 'One realm we have never conquered: the pure present.', 178, 0), (419912, 'He who lives in the present lives in eternity.', 1163, 0), (419913, 'I am in the present. I cannot know what tomorrow will bring forth. I can know only what the truth is for me today. That is what I am called upon to serve.', 16868, 0), (419914, 'The present offers itself to our touch for only an instant of time and then eludes the senses.', 4891, 0), (419915, 'A life uncommanded now is uncom-manded  a life unenjoyed now is unenjoyed  a life not lived wisely now is not lived wisely.', 10420, 0), (419916, 'The word "now" is like a bomb thrown through the window  and it ticks.', 2477, 0), (419917, 'Whether it''s the best of times or the worst of times  it''s the only time we''ve got.', 44013, 0), (419918, 'It is now  and in this world  that we must live.', 8, 0), (419919, 'Who cares about great marks left behind? We have one life.... Just one. Our life. We have nothing else.', 61075, 0), (419920, 'This-the immediate  everyday  and present experience-is IT  the entire and ultimate point for the existence of a universe.', 45466, 0), (419921, 'Let us live today.', 62240, 0), (419922, 'Work accomplished means little. It is in the past. What we all want is the glorious and living present.', 12805, 0), (419923, 'Yesterday is a cancelled check. Tomorrow is a promissory note. Today is cash in hand. Spend It!', 65967, 0), (419924, 'Today Relative to Yesterday or Tomorrow The future is made of the same stuff as the present.', 1662, 0), (419925, 'Yesterday is but a dream  tomorrow is only a vision. But today  well lived  makes every yesterday a dream of happiness  and every tomorrow a vision of hope. Look well  therefore  to this day  for it is life  the very life of life.', 65968, 0), (419926, 'Be glad today. Tomorrow may bring tears. Be brave today. The darkest night will pass. And golden rays will usher in the dawn.', 44834, 0), (419927, 'Do not look back on happiness  or dream of it in the future. You are only sure of today  do not let yourself be cheated out of it.', 2175, 0), (419928, 'Existence is no more than the precarious attainment of relevance in an intensely mobile flux of past  present  and future.', 4673, 0), (419929, 'I am not afraid of tomorrow  for I have seen yesterday and I love today.', 53013, 0), (419930, 'The past  the present and the future are really one: they are today.', 3252, 0), (419931, 'The present contains all that there is. It is holy ground  for it is the past  and it is the future.', 2606, 0), (419932, 'There is no justification for present existence other than its expansion into an indefinitely open future.', 477, 0), (419933, 'With the past  I have nothing to do  nor with the future. I live now.', 760, 0), (419934, 'Children have neither a past nor a future. Thus they enjoy the present  which seldom happens to us.', 5879, 0), (419935, 'The past is a bucket of ashes  so live not in your yesterdays  nor just for tomorrow  but in the here and now.', 1301, 0), (419936, 'Youth is the time of getting  middle age of improving  and old age of spending.', 1211, 0), (419937, 'It is not the weight of the future or the past that is pressing upon you  but ever that of the present alone. Even this burden  too  can be lessened if you confine it strictly to its own limits.', 267, 0), (419938, 'Reappraise the past  reevaluate where we''ve been  clarify where we are  and predict or anticipate where we are headed.', 9838, 0), (419939, 'We can easily manage if we will only take  each day  the burden appointed to it. But the load will be too heavy for us if we carry yesterday''s burden over again today  and then add the burden of the morrow before we are required to bear it.', 1850, 0), (419940, 'Take in the ideas of the day  drain off those of yesterday. As to the morrow  time enough to consider it when it becomes today.', 5223, 0), (419941, 'Tomorrow I will live  the fool does say  today itself''s too late  the wise lived yesterday.', 62597, 0), (419942, 'The cares of today are seldom those of tomorrow.', 8676, 0), (419943, 'Yesterday is a cancelled check  tomorrow is a promissory note  today is the only cash you have-so spend it wisely.', 65969, 0), (419944, 'Everyman''s life lies within the present  for the past is spent and done with  and the future is uncertain.', 267, 0), (419945, 'The flesh endures the storms of the present alone  the mind those of the past and future as well.', 1839, 0), (419946, 'I try to learn from the past  but I plan for the future by focusing exclusively on the present. That''s where the fun is.', 64643, 0), (419947, 'No mind is much employed upon the present  recollection and anticipation fill up almost all our moments.', 2087, 0), (419948, 'The only living life is in the past and future-the present is an interlude- strange interlude in which we call on past and future to bear witness that we are living.', 6194, 0), (419949, 'Past  and to come  seems best  things present  worst.', 13, 0), (419950, 'The past cannot be regained  although we can 